  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training, Coordination and Empowerment of Rural Women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Working women in the rural northeast live with a strong patriarchal culture, face devaluation of their productive activities, and are exposed to situations that violate their rights. Because these women are mostly black, they are also more vulnerable to situations of discrimination and difficulties in accessing public policies and positions of power. Movimiento de la Mujer Trabajadora Rural del Nordeste &#x2014; or the Movement of the Rural Working Women of the North East &#x2014; seeks to empower these women and construct fairer, more equal gender relations. This project follows that example by supporting training for female educators in nine states of the northeast. Additionally, it will support income generation, and contribute to strengthening policy advocacy actions. The project will directly involve 36 leaders (directors and coordinators) and 495 women who are rural workers. Another 3,375 working rural women will be involved by passing on the gift.</narrative>
  </description>
